  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nWhen running the private optimism setup with the relayer container enabled, it crashes with an internal error.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. Go to `/ops`\r\n2. Run `docker-compose -f docker-compose-nobuild.yml -f docker-compose.yml up --scale relayer=1 -d`\r\n3. Wait a bit\r\n4. Check `relayer` logs to see error:\r\n```\r\n$ docker-compose logs -f relayer\r\nops-relayer-1  | node:internal/modules/cjs/loader:936\r\nops-relayer-1  |   throw err;\r\nops-relayer-1  |   ^\r\nops-relayer-1  |\r\nops-relayer-1  | Error: Cannot find module '/opt/optimism/packages/message-relayer/exec/run-message-relayer.js'\r\nops-relayer-1  |     at Function.Module._resolveFilename (node:internal/modules/cjs/loader:933:15)\r\nops-relayer-1  |     at Function.Module._load (node:internal/modules/cjs/loader:778:27)\r\nops-relayer-1  |     at Function.executeUserEntryPoint [as runMain] (node:internal/modules/run_main:81:12)\r\nops-relayer-1  |     at node:internal/main/run_main_module:17:47 {\r\nops-relayer-1  |   code: 'MODULE_NOT_FOUND',\r\nops-relayer-1  |   requireStack: []\r\nops-relayer-1  | }\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nThe relayer should work\r\n\r\n",
